No one who is not the son oi Christ and Peter can be Pope. This cannot be the result of an election made by men, and so such an election has no power to make aPope. That a man chosen by the Western Church should receive the name of Pope is an abuse3 it has no Scripture warrant, and the title has been introduced by a secular law. But does the choice of men give a greater right than the choice of God? Why, even Christ's choice, as we see in the case of Judas Iscariot, does not necessarily mean eternal predestination and perfect grace.
